The paper deals with optimization of a general objective function over rectangular matrices of low rank, which is a common problem in machine learning and signal processing. The paper also discusses the use of iterative optimization algorithms such as gradient descent. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves analysis of the global geometry of the objective function, which suggests the possibility of using geometric algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a likely category as well. Finally, the paper discusses the application of the results to matrix completion and sensing, which falls under cs.SI (Signal Processing).
